class="section-faq"><div
class="container"><h2 id=fAQs class="section-heading">FAQs:</h2><div
class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-can-i-make-myself-incorporated class="question">How can I make myself incorporated?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li><a
href="#decide-which-state-to-incorporate-in">Decide where to incorporate</a>.</li><li><a
href="#find-a-business-name">Select a business name and do a business name search</a>.</li><li><a
href="#form-your-business">Decide on the type of corporation you want to form</a>.</li><li><a
href="#appoint-a-registered-agent">Appoint a registered agent</a>.</li><li><a
href="#prepare-and-file-articles-of-incorporation">Prepare and file Articles of Incorporation</a>.</li><li><a
href="#create-corporate-bylaws">Create corporate bylaws</a>.</li><li><a
href="#hold-the-first-board-meeting">Hold the first meeting</a>.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The fees for filing articles of incorporation vary by <a
href="#guides-to-starting-a-business-by-state">state</a> but generally lie between $250.00 and $500.00. Contact your local secretary of state office for more information about the fees applicable in your state.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-long-does-it-take-to-incorporate class="question">How long does it take to incorporate?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>This can vary according to the state. In some states, it takes three or more weeks to incorporate. Incorporating online tends to be the fastest way to establish a corporation, often only taking between one and three days.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-is-a-company-incorporated class="question">How is a company incorporated?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>A company can be incorporated by filing articles of incorporation with the secretary of state. However, before this can be done you should have selected a name for the business, completed a business name search, and appointed a registered agent.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-long-does-it-take-to-incorporate-in-canada class="question">How long does it take to incorporate in Canada?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Incorporating in Canada can take as little as one to two days.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=why-would-someone-incorporate-themselves class="question">Why would someone incorporate themselves?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>There are several benefits to incorporating a sole proprietorship, such as to protect personal assets, add credibility to the business, and to attract investors.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-039-s-better-an-llc-or-corporation class="question">What&#039;s better, an LLC or corporation?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Corporations and LLCs both limit the owners' liability but they are owned, managed, and taxed differently. Each business type offers its own set of advantages and disadvantages that must be considered before deciding which is better for your business.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-incorporate-online class="question">How do I incorporate online?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Look up your state office for incorporation, which is usually the secretary of state, and search for a link to start the registration process. You will first have to make all the necessary preparations, such as selecting a business name, conducting a business name search, and appointing a registered agent, before you can complete the articles of incorporation with all the necessary information.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-the-benefits-of-incorporating-yourself class="question">What are the benefits of incorporating yourself?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>There are several advantages to incorporating a sole proprietorship, such as to protect personal assets, add credibility to the business, and to attract investors.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-i-start-a-corporation-with-one-person class="question">Can I start a corporation with one person?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, a corporation can have only one owner or shareholder.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate-in-canada class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate in Canada?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The service fees for incorporating in Canada are $200.00 for filing online and $250.00 for filing by paper.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-you-incorporate-a-sole-proprietorship class="question">Can you incorporate a sole proprietorship?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, you can incorporate a sole proprietorship.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-the-difference-between-llc-and-s-corp class="question">What is the difference between LLC and S Corp?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>LLCs and S corps both offer limited liability protection and qualify for pass-through taxation. And while LLCs can have any number of members, S corps are restricted to 100 shareholders who must be U.S. citizens or residents. An advantage of an S corp is that stock is freely transferable, which is not the case with an LLC.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=which-state-is-cheapest-to-incorporate-in class="question">Which state is cheapest to incorporate in?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Arkansas, Colorado, Hawaii, and Iowa have among the lowest filing fees for forming a corporation.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-the-best-way-to-incorporate-a-small-business class="question">What is the best way to incorporate a small business?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The easiest way to incorporate a business is through an online incorporation service such as Incfile.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-start-an-s-corporation class="question">How much does it cost to start an S corporation?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>To establish an S corporation you will first have to form a C corporation for which the filing fees vary by state, in the general range of $50.00 to $250.00, and then apply for S corporation status with the IRS.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate-in-pa class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate in PA?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Filing Articles of Incorporation in Pennsylvania costs $125.00.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate-in-delaware class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate in Delaware?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Filing articles of incorporation in Delaware costs a minimum of $89.00.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-file-articles-of-incorporation class="question">How do I file articles of incorporation?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>In most states, you have to file articles of incorporation accompanied by a fee with the secretary of state. This can usually be done by paper or online. Do an online search to find out where and how to incorporate in your state.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-the-difference-between-llc-and-inc class="question">What is the difference between LLC and INC?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The main difference between the two is that corporations have shareholders, issue share of stock which allows for an easier way to raise capital, and are subject to corporate tax. LLCs, on the other hand, are owned by individuals and do not allow for the free transfer of ownership but do qualify for pass-through taxation.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-does-it-mean-to-be-incorporated class="question">What does it mean to be incorporated?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Incorporating a business means to create a legal business structure that is separate from its owners or shareholders.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-change-from-c-corp-to-s-corp class="question">How do I change from C Corp to S Corp?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Once you have established a C corporation you will have to file Form 2553 with the IRS to apply for S corporation status.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate-a-nonprofit class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate a nonprofit?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The cost of incorporating a nonprofit varies by state. State filing fees generally range from $50.00 to $250.00.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-long-does-it-take-to-file-an-s-corp class="question">How long does it take to file an S Corp?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The processing time for incorporating a business generally takes 3 to 6 weeks, although incorporating online can be significantly faster. After incorporating your business you will have to apply for S corporation status with the IRS. You can expect to wait up to 60 days to receive your S corporation application determination from the IRS.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=should-i-incorporate-my-small-business class="question">Should I incorporate my small business?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>The decision to incorporate should not be made lightly. There are several advantages as well as disadvantages to incorporating a small business instead of forming an LLC or remaining a sole proprietorship or partnership. If your small business is growing rapidly and you intend to go public at some point, incorporating may be a good decision.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-the-difference-between-corporation-and-incorporated class="question">What is the difference between corporation and incorporated?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>There is no difference in the legal structure of businesses that are defined as a corporation or incorporated.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=when-should-you-incorporate-a-startup class="question">When should you incorporate a startup?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>It is generally advisable for a startup to incorporate or form an LLC early on. However, this may also depend on the type of ownership, size, and projected growth rate of the business. Familiarize yourself with the benefits and drawbacks of the different types of legal business structures to gain a better understanding of which structure is the best choice for your business.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-an-incorporator-be-a-director class="question">Can an incorporator be a director?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, an incorporator can also serve as a director.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-much-does-it-cost-to-incorporate-in-tennessee class="question">How much does it cost to incorporate in Tennessee?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Filing articles of incorporation in Tennessee costs a minimum of $100.00.</p></div></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I make myself incorporated?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#decide-which-state-to-incorporate-in\">Decide where to incorporate<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#find-a-business-name\">Select a business name and do a business name search<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#form-your-business\">Decide on the type of corporation you want to form<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#appoint-a-registered-agent\">Appoint a registered agent<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#prepare-and-file-articles-of-incorporation\">Prepare and file Articles of Incorporation<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#create-corporate-bylaws\">Create corporate bylaws<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"#hold-the-first-board-meeting\">Hold the first meeting<\/a>.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does it cost to incorporate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>The fees for filing articles of incorporation vary by <a href=\"#guides-to-starting-a-business-by-state\">state<\/a> but generally lie between $250.00 and $500.00. Contact your local secretary of state office for more information about the fees applicable in your state.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does it take to incorporate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>This can vary according to the state. In some states, it takes three or more weeks to incorporate. Incorporating online tends to be the fastest way to establish a corporation, often only taking between one and three days.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is a company incorporated?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>A company can be incorporated by filing articles of incorporation with the secretary of state. However, before this can be done you should have 